From: Bob Van Valzah <bob@vanvalzah.com>
Subject: [PATCH v3] igc: disable TX timestamping around TIMINCA write in adjfine

igc_ptp_adjfine_i225() writes IGC_TIMINCA without synchronization.
When the hardware captures a TX timestamp while TIMINCA is changing,
the captured value is corrupt, causing "Tx timestamp timeout" after
15 seconds and eventually wedging the EXTTS subsystem.

The race is between software and hardware — no software lock alone
can prevent the hardware's asynchronous TX timestamp capture from
reading TIMINCA at the instant software writes it (confirmed by
testing: tmreg_lock alone does not fix the bug).

Fix: hold tmreg_lock (consistent with all other timing register
accesses), temporarily disable TX timestamping in hardware by
clearing IGC_TSYNCTXCTL_ENABLED, write TIMINCA, then re-enable.
This prevents the hardware from starting any new TX timestamp
capture during the rate change.

The disable window is ~1 µs (two register writes around the TIMINCA
write).  Any TX packet sent during this window simply won't receive
a hardware timestamp — no corruption, no timeout, no wedge.  At
realistic PTP sync rates (128 Hz), the probability of a packet
landing in this window is < 0.013%.

v3: Disable/re-enable TX timestamping around TIMINCA write instead
    of checking pending skbs (v1) or using tmreg_lock alone (v2).
    Always succeeds (no -EBUSY), no adjfine starvation under load.

Signed-off-by: Bob Van Valzah <bob@vanvalzah.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igc/igc_ptp.c | 14 +++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 13 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igc/igc_ptp.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igc/igc_ptp.c
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igc/igc_ptp.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igc/igc_ptp.c
@@ -47,6 +47,8 @@ static int igc_ptp_adjfine_i225(struct ptp_clock_info *ptp, long scaled_ppm)
 {
 	struct igc_adapter *igc = container_of(ptp, struct igc_adapter,
 					       ptp_caps);
 	struct igc_hw *hw = &igc->hw;
+	unsigned long flags;
+	u32 txctl;
 	int neg_adj = 0;
 	u64 rate;
 	u32 inca;
@@ -63,7 +65,17 @@ static int igc_ptp_adjfine_i225(struct ptp_clock_info *ptp, long scaled_ppm)
 	if (neg_adj)
 		inca |= ISGN;

-	wr32(IGC_TIMINCA, inca);
+	/* Changing TIMINCA while the hardware is capturing a TX timestamp
+	 * corrupts the timestamp, causing "Tx timestamp timeout."
+	 * Temporarily disable TX timestamping so no new capture can start
+	 * during the rate change.
+	 */
+	spin_lock_irqsave(&igc->tmreg_lock, flags);
+	txctl = rd32(IGC_TSYNCTXCTL);
+	wr32(IGC_TSYNCTXCTL, txctl & ~IGC_TSYNCTXCTL_ENABLED);
+	wr32(IGC_TIMINCA, inca);
+	wr32(IGC_TSYNCTXCTL, txctl);
+	spin_unlock_irqrestore(&igc->tmreg_lock, flags);

 	return 0;
 }
